race.description: Keeneland November Breeding Stock Sale Hcp
race.comment: THE REPLICANT (3) was hemmed in on the rails last start and never saw clear running in a total forgive run over this distance at the Kensington track. Drove hard late to just miss over 1400m here the run prior. Finds a mediocre race today and if his fortunes change a well-deserved win looks on the cards. FRONTEX (2) got clear when the bird had flow at this track last time out, clocking-in fourth over the mile. Back in trip but is coming off a four-week break with blinkers on so should be sharp enough to run a big race. BELIEVE IN ANGELS (6) found the line well in a similar race at the Kenso a fortnight ago. Goes well here so must be respected. BARTOLF (1) with McDonald aboard comes under notice. Racing well, filling a minor placing at Rosehill last time off a 33-day break. Sure to be there at the business end. CLIMB THE LADDER (4) has been going okay in Victoria and that form should stack up.
